The Lagos State Government through the Directorate of Citizens’ Rights (DCR) has rescued a 12-year-old boy in Agege area of Lagos State from his parents over alleged abuse. The government which made this public on Monday, through a press statement issued by the Director of DCR, Mrs. Biola Oseni, stated that its attention was drawn to the case through a photograph on social media platform, Facebook. In the message that was trending the boy was covered with blood all over his body. He was rescued at No. 64 Moricass Road Agege. According to the Director, during a visit of officials of the Ministry, to the boy’s home it was gathered that he was assaulted by his mother who beat him up. “The rescue team did not meet the mother but she was later sighted at a different location and was apprehended by government officials who took her to the police for questioning,” she added. Mrs. Oseni further disclosed that when the matter was reported at the police station, the woman’s husband was mandated to produce the boy while the woman was at the police station. According to her, the woman will be charged to court on Tuesday, 3 March 2020 while the boy would be taken to the Ministry of Youth and Social Development for necessary action and be placed in one of government’s facility. 